  "time_ut": 1661759102,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3 \u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The minister explained the reason for the hike in the electricity bill",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister Kanjana Wijesekara said in the Parliament today (29) that although the increase in electricity tariff is difficult for the people, considering the cost, the tariff hike must be done.",
        "He said this during an adjournment debate on the government's decision to increase electricity tariffs.",
        "He also said that despite the hike in electricity charges, relief has been given to low-income earners.",
        "He said that some of the work that could be done by the Electricity Board had been given to other departments in the past, and there were times when he stood alone and fought against the mafias in the board.",
        "He said that there are huge problems regarding the salaries and allowances of the Electricity Board and Petroleum Corporation employees and these companies are giving 25% salary increase to the employees every year without any service evaluation."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
      "body_line_ents_list": [
